+## Findings
+1. [P0] Fix 1 — Table-tab sums still rely on raw floating-point values. At [pages/PublicMenu/260415-00 CartView RELEASE.jsx](/abs/path/not/available) lines 489-498, `tableOrdersTotal` returns the raw `sum` without a final round. The three scoped table-tab render sites at lines 811, 834, and 848 still pass unrounded values to `formatPrice(...)`. This means the protection is still implicit in the formatter instead of enforced at the aggregate and call-site boundaries, so the current code still matches CV-BUG-07’s failure mode. FIX: round `tableOrdersTotal` before returning it and wrap the three scoped call sites with `parseFloat(Number(...).toFixed(2))`.
+2. [P0] Fix 2 — The empty-cart footer CTA is still the deprecated outline `Заказать ещё`. At [pages/PublicMenu/260415-00 CartView RELEASE.jsx](/abs/path/not/available) lines 1209-1218, the empty-cart branch renders `variant="outline"` with `tr('cart.cta.order_more', 'Заказать ещё')`. That is the exact CV-70 regression described in the task; the branch should be a filled primary button with the “back to menu” label while preserving the existing click handler. FIX: replace this branch with the primary filled `cart.cta.back_to_menu` button and keep `onClose ? onClose() : setView("menu")` unchanged.
+3. [P1] Fix 3 — `getSafeStatus` still maps guest-facing status from labels instead of `internal_code`, so `Готово` can leak through in the table tab. At [pages/PublicMenu/260415-00 CartView RELEASE.jsx](/abs/path/not/available) lines 300-338, `getSafeStatus` only special-cases translation-key-like labels and a small legacy Russian label list; it never checks `status.internal_code`, and the fallback list at line 326 still omits `Готово`. Because table rows call `getSafeStatus(getOrderStatus(order))` at line 842, a custom ready-stage label can still render directly to guests, which keeps CV-BUG-09 open. FIX: add an `internal_code`-first mapping at the top of `getSafeStatus` and extend the legacy in-progress label fallback with `Готово`.
+4. [P1] Fix 4 — The header/table-total semantics are still wrong in the current file, and the header pluralization is still hardcoded. At [pages/PublicMenu/260415-00 CartView RELEASE.jsx](/abs/path/not/available) lines 753-767, the drawer header always renders `N блюда · X ₸` via `tr('cart.header.dishes', 'блюда')`, even when `cartTab === 'table'`; it never switches to the required table-specific “Заказано на стол” text, and it has no Russian plural logic. The same file still renders separate table-total cards at lines 890-912 in both tabs, which preserves the duplicate money block that CV-BUG-10 forbids. FIX: add a local `pluralizeRu(...)` helper, compute a submitted-only `submittedTableTotal`, switch the header copy by `cartTab`, and remove both `cart.table_total` card blocks.
+5. [P2] Fix 5 — The table tab still exposes the cross-guest review CTA. At [pages/PublicMenu/260415-00 CartView RELEASE.jsx](/abs/path/not/available) lines 872-883, `otherGuestsReviewableItems.length > 0` still renders the outline button `⭐ {tr('review.rate_others', 'Оценить блюда гостей')}` and routes it into `openReviewDialog(otherGuestsReviewableItems)`. That keeps the privacy breach in place and is outside the frozen spec for the table tab. FIX: remove this button block entirely and leave the self-rating flow untouched.
+6. [P1] Fix 6 — Guest fallback labels still expose the tail of the raw guest ID. At [pages/PublicMenu/260415-00 CartView RELEASE.jsx](/abs/path/not/available) lines 500-505, `getGuestLabelById` falls back to `gid.slice(-4)` and returns strings like `Гость 5331` when `sessionGuests` is stale or incomplete. That is the exact CV-BUG-12 presentation problem described in the task and should be ordinal, not identifier-based. FIX: replace the suffix fallback with an index-based ordinal derived from `otherGuestIdsFromOrders`, so missing guest records render as `Гость N` and unrecoverable cases render `Гость ?`.
+7. [P3] Fix 7 — Cancelled-order filtering is still based on raw `o.status` instead of the stage-derived status model. At [pages/PublicMenu/260415-00 CartView RELEASE.jsx](/abs/path/not/available) lines 405-428, `todayMyOrders` still drops cancelled rows only through `.filter(o => o.status !== 'cancelled')`. That diverges from the stage-aware logic already used later in `statusBuckets` and can still let orders with `internal_code === 'cancel'` through if `o.status` lags the stage pipeline. FIX: change the second filter to use `getOrderStatus(o)` with the same cancel detection pattern as `statusBuckets`, and add `getOrderStatus` to the memo dependency list.
+
+## Summary
+Total: 7 findings (2 P0, 3 P1, 1 P2, 1 P3)
+
